      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw in-scope domain constraint",
      "description": "Assessment applies exclusively to non-cannulated titanium-alloy pedicle screws with nominal diameter 7.5 mm and shank length 45–55 mm, tested or simulated under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading in a two-level corpectomy construct configuration. Cannulated variants, screws outside the stated dimensional envelope, and dynamic fatigue loading conditions are explicitly excluded from this COU."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 compression-bending operating envelope",
      "description": "Applied compressive load range: 0–2500 N axial with superimposed bending moment up to 22 Nm at a crosshead displacement rate of 5 mm/min ± 0.5 mm/min. Ambient temperature: 23 ± 2 °C. Construct span (superior to inferior vertebral body block centre): 100 ± 2 mm. Screw insertion torque: 4.0 ± 0.5 Nm. Material elastic modulus input: Ti-6Al-4V ELI, 114 ± 3 GPa; yield strength 880 ± 20 MPa. Mesh element size: 0.4–0.8 mm in critical stress regions. Boundary conditions: fixed base block, load applied at superior block centroid."
    }
  },
